  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, IClassifier<double[]>, IFixableClassifier<double[]>, IFixableUpdatableClassifier<double[]>, IFixedClassifier<double[]>, IUpdatableClassifier<double[]>, ITaggedEntity
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    CosineDistanceMergeKNNClassifier, EuclidianDistanceMergeKNNClassifier, L1DistanceMergeKNNClassifier, LpDistanceMergeKNNClassifier

    public class KNNClassifier
extends AbstractFixableFeatureExtractingUpdatableClassifier<double[],double[]>
implements IFixableUpdatableClassifier<double[]>
    Extends the super class to implement a nearest neighbor classifier using various distance metrics. Neighborhoods are identified by clusters of features.
    Author:
    wangshiq, dawood

        protected FixedKNNClassifier trainFixedClassifierOnFeatures(Iterable<? extends ILabeledFeatureGram<double[]>[]> featureWithLabels)
                                                     throws AISPException
        Description copied from class: AbstractFixableFeatureExtractingClassifier
        Build the classifier from the given set of features. If this is called, then the iterable has at least one feature array in it. AbstractFixableFeatureExtractingClassifier.primaryTrainingLabel has been set to the value passed to AbstractFixableClassifier.train(String, Iterable) when this is called and should be used by the implementation to define the labels on which the model is trained.
        Specified by:
        trainFixedClassifierOnFeatures in class AbstractFixableFeatureExtractingClassifier<double[],double[]>
        Parameters:
        featureWithLabels - the iterable over arrays of labeled features. Each array of features corresponds to an individual training sample as provided to AbstractFixableFeatureExtractingClassifier.trainFixedClassifierOnData(String, Iterable) as part of the iterable provided there.
        Returns:
        never null.

        AISPException
